{"author":{"id":"b5488c8014f6e3c5b881ab15bd157ab69f5f57336ea260bfb0e82983ebd7b615"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1739440659,"nonce":"8u6QqAHu/4iMQfVbCswKqTkx0uI=","metadata":{"github-id":"I_kwDOAW4Y0s6p59We","github-url":"https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/issues/6755","origin":"github"},"title":"Split character column based on regular expression or delimiter","message":"It would be nice to have a tool allowing to split a character column into (multiple) new columns based on a separator or regex.\n\nAn example would be I have dataframe like this:\n\n```r\nvar\tvalue\nUbi4_1\t26.17\nUbi4_2\t26.30\nUbi4_3\t22.88\n```\n\nI would like to split `var` column by \"_\" into `condition` and `replicate` columns, so the final result would be:\n\n```r\ncond\trep \tvalue\nUbi4\t1\t26.17\nUbi4\t2\t26.30\nUbi4\t3\t22.88\n```\n\nIn R, this can be achieved using e.g. the `separate` function from tidyr package or its [modifications](https://tidyr.tidyverse.org/reference/separate_wider_delim.html).\n\nThanks for considering!","files":null}]}